text: Hey Gura! I hope you feel better soon! Thanks for the fun stream even though you're under the weather. Once you get to post game, a water team becomes even more viable in competitive PvP. Pelipper with the Drizzle ability causes it to start raining when it enters the battle and boost water type moves. You could also include pokemon like Kingdra who has the swift swim ability to double it's speed when it's raining. Whiscash also has an ability that let's it heal status conditions in the rain, meaning it can use rest, fully recover it's HP, and then immediately wake back up. Tentacruel has an ability called Rain Dish, which heals it's HP by 1/16 every turn it's raining. If you were to make Tentacruel tanky and give it a move like toxic, it would be difficult to deal with. You could also get Blastoise post game with the Rain Dish ability for another tanky pokemon that's difficult to deal with. Just some ideas since you're going for the all water run. Good luck and have fun out there champ!
